I&#x27;m sure it does, but I can write the same class in C# just as easily:<p><pre><code>    class Person
    {
        public int Sanity { get; set; }

        public Person()
        {
            Sanity = 50;
        }
    }
</code></pre>
And to call it:<p><pre><code>    var programmer = new Person();
    programmer.Sanity += 1000000;
    Console.WriteLine(programmer.Sanity);
</code></pre>
